25%20as%20of%20February%202024%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.federalreserve.gov%2Freleases%2Fg19%2Fcurrent%2F%5C%22%3Eper%20the%20Federal%20Reserve%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20carrying%20any%20amount%20of%20credit%20card%20debt%20can%20become%20costly%20in%20a%20hurry.%20Fortunately%2C%20there%20are%20ways%20to%20erase%20credit%20card%20debt%20or%20at%20least%20get%20it%20under%20control%2C%20such%20as%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fbest-personal-loans%5C%22%3Epersonal%20loan%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20experts%20also%20recommend%20consolidating%20high-interest%20credit%20card%20debt%20onto%20a%20personal%20loan%2C%20as%20these%20loans%20often%20offer%20lower%20interest%20rates.%20Other%20types%20of%20loans%20commonly%20used%20for%20debt%20consolidation%20include%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fwhat-is-a-home-equity-loan%5C%22%3Ehome%20equity%20loans%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20HELOCs%2C%20and%20even%20401(k)%20loans.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20thing%20is%2C%20debt%20consolidation%20doesn't%20always%20work%2C%20and%20for%20more%20reasons%20than%20one.%20According%20to%20Howard%20Dvorkin%20of%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fdebt.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDebt.com%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%26quot%3Ball%20it%20takes%20is%20human%20nature%26quot%3B%20for%20the%20best-laid%20debt%20payoff%20plan%20to%20fall%20apart.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECan%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fwhat-is-debt-consolidation%5C%22%3Edebt%20consolidation%3C%2Fa%3E%20loan%20actually%20make%20debt%20worse%3F%20Financial%20experts%20say%20the%20answer%20is%20yes%2C%20for%20four%20reasons.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E1.%20You're%20not%20paying%20off%20the%20debt%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EDvorkin%20points%20out%20that%20debt%20consolidation%20with%20a%20loan%20moves%20the%20money%20you%20owe%20onto%20a%20single%20loan%20that%20likely%20has%20a%20lower%20interest%20rate%2C%20but%20%26quot%3Byou%20haven't%20lowered%20your%20principal.%26quot%3B%20This%20puts%20you%20in%20a%20position%20where%20you're%20playing%20a%20shell%20game%20with%20your%20debt%20%E2%80%94%20one%20where%20you%20still%20owe%20as%20much%20as%20when%20you%20started.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPersonal%20loans%20for%20debt%20consolidation%20often%20come%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fwhat-is-an-origination-fee%5C%22%3Eorigination%20fees%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20is%20usually%20a%20percentage%20of%20the%20loan%20amount.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E2.%20You%20can%20still%20fall%20behind%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EConsider%20a%20scenario%20where%20someone%20gets%20a%20debt%20consolidation%20loan%2C%20but%20then%20they're%20laid%20off%20or%20they're%20in%20a%20serious%20car%20accident.%20Suddenly%2C%20they%20can't%20keep%20up%20with%20payments%2C%20causing%20their%20account%20to%20go%20to%20collections.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTheir%20credit%20score%20tanks%2C%20which%20means%20they%20can't%20get%20another%20debt%20consolidation%20loan%20or%20even%20a%20credit%20card%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Dvorkin.%20%26quot%3BNow%20they're%20worse%20off%20than%20they%20were%20before.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E3.%20Debt%20consolidation%20doesn't%20solve%20spending%20issues%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFinancial%20expert%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fandreaworoch.com%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAndrea%20Woroch%3C%2Fa%3E%20points%20out%20that%20debt%20consolidation%20may%20be%20nothing%20more%20than%20a%20Band-Aid%20if%20you%20don't%20identify%20and%20fix%20the%20poor%20money%20management%20habits%20that%20got%20you%20into%20debt%20in%20the%20first%20place.%20If%20you%20keep%20spending%20as%20normal%20after%20you%20consolidate%20debt%2C%20you%20could%20easily%20rack%20up%20even%20more%20debt%20than%20you%20started%20with%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20why%20financial%20advisor%20Kendall%20Meade%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fsofi-bank-review%5C%22%3ESoFi%3C%2Fa%3E%20always%20recommends%20halting%20credit%20card%20use%20for%20people%20who%20consolidate%20debt%20with%20any%20type%20of%20loan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20have%20seen%20many%20people%20consolidate%20their%20debts%20into%20a%20loan%20but%20then%20continue%20to%20run%20the%20credit%20cards%20back%20up%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Meade.%20%26quot%3BNow%20they%20have%20double%20the%20payments%20and%20may%20not%20have%20the%20option%20to%20consolidate%20again%20making%20it%20much%20harder%20for%20them%20to%20get%20out%20of%20debt.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E4.%20Some%20debt%20consolidation%20loans%20have%20additional%20risks%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFinally%2C%20remember%20that%20some%20types%20of%20loans%20you%20can%20use%20for%20debt%20consolidation%20have%20a%20unique%20set%20of%20risks.%20Anne%20Lester%2C%20author%20of%20%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BYour%20Best%20Financial%20Life%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%20and%20former%20Head%20of%20Retirement%20Solutions%20for%20JPMorgan%20Asset%20Management%2C%20said%20that%20this%20is%20definitely%20the%20case%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2F401k-loan%5C%22%3E401(k)%20loans%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20let%20consumers%20borrow%20from%20their%20own%20retirement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20borrowing%20against%20a%20401(k)%20can%20give%20people%20access%20to%20cash%20for%20debt%20consolidation%2C%20Lester%20said%20that%20most%20of%20these%20loans%20need%20to%20be%20repaid%20over%20a%20relatively%20short%20timeline.%20Borrowers%20also%20have%20to%20repay%20the%20loan%20with%20after-tax%20income.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELester%20also%20said%20that%20someone%20who%20voluntarily%20leaves%20or%20loses%20their%20job%20will%20need%20to%20repay%20the%20entire%20loan%20immediately%20to%20avoid%20having%20it%20treated%20as%20a%20withdrawal.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20they%20can't%20repay%20the%20loan%20right%20away%2C%20%26quot%3Bthey%20will%20owe%20income%20taxes%20and%20an%20additional%2010%25%20early%20withdrawal%20penalty%20if%20they%20are%20below%20the%20age%20of%2059%C2%BD%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20risks%20apply%20to%20home%20equity%20products.%20While%20home%20equity%20loans%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fheloc-pros-and-cons%5C%22%3EHELOCs%3C%2Fa%3E%20may%20offer%20attractive%20rates%20and%20flexible%20repayment%20terms%2C%20they%20use%20the%20value%20of%20your%20home%20as%20collateral.%20This%20means%20you%20could%20lose%20your%20home%20to%20foreclosure%20if%20you%20fail%20to%20pay%20the%20money%20back.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAll%20these%20risks%20aside%2C%20consolidating%20debt%20onto%20a%20loan%20with%20a%20lower%20interest%20rate%20can%20still%20work.%20The%20key%20to%20getting%20ahead%20with%20this%20strategy%20is%20having%20a%20plan%20in%20place%20ahead%20of%20time%20and%20sticking%20to%20it%20no%20matter%20what%20life%20throws%20your%20way.%20A%20good%20first%20step%20is%20talking%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Ffinancial-planning%5C%22%3Efinancial%20planner%3C%2Fa%3E%20about%20your%20unique%20situation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffinancial-experts-debt-consolidation-helps-with-credit-card-debt-2024-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1716032341000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F664665c520abc1efe8fac03d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffinancial-experts-debt-consolidation-helps-with-credit-card-debt-2024-5%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22If%20you%20want%20to%20get%20ahead%20of%20your%20credit%20card%20debt%2C%20a%20debt%20consolidation%20loan%20can%20help%2C%20but%20it%20can%20also%20cause%20just%20as%20many%20problems%20as%20it%20fixes.%22%2C%22autho