%20for%20the%20person%20in%20front%20of%20you%20and%20trusting%20the%20person%20behind%20you%20to%20check%20your%20chute.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20each%20jump%2C%20you're%20generally%20exiting%20from%20both%20parachute%20doors%20of%20an%20aircraft%2C%20and%20each%20door%20will%20have%20a%20jumpmaster.%20Once%20the%20green%20light%20comes%20on%2C%20meaning%20that%20we're%20safe%20to%20exit%20paratroopers%2C%20most%20people%20click%20right%20into%20their%20training%20and%20know%20what%20they're%20doing.%20They've%20prepped%20for%20this.%20They're%20ready%20to%20go.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEach%20trooper%20gets%20three%20opportunities%20to%20go%20and%20if%20they%20don't%20go%2C%20for%20whatever%20reason%2C%20they're%20getting%20removed%20from%20the%20door%20and%20told%20not%20to%20touch%20their%20equipment.%20They'll%20fly%20back%2C%20and%20then%20a%20jumpmaster%20who%20wasn't%20a%20part%20of%20the%20team%20will%20look%20at%20their%20equipment%20and%20chute%20thoroughly%20for%20a%20technical%20inspection.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBasically%2C%20we%20want%20to%20make%20sure%20we're%20giving%20the%20paratrooper%20every%20benefit%20of%20the%20doubt%20that%20they%20didn't%20just%20get%20scared%20before%20the%20jump%20but%20maybe%20found%20something%20wrong%20in%20their%20equipment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20nothing%20is%20wrong%2C%20it%20goes%20up%20a%20chain%20of%20command%20to%20make%20a%20determination%20whether%20that%20trooper%20should%20do%20some%20remedial%20training%20or%20a%20larger%20discussion%20about%20the%20mission%20and%20what's%20expected%20of%20them.%20This%20is%20all%20exceedingly%20rare%2C%20but%20there%20is%20a%20plan%20if%20it%20does%20come%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22be745dff-7ed2-4cae-81f5-73022ccece5a%5C%22%3EHitting%20the%20ground%20the%20right%20way%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Paratroopers%20with%202nd%20Infantry%20Brigade%20Combat%20Team%20(Airborne)%2C%2011th%20Airborne%20Division%2C%20stage%20onboard%20a%20Boeing%2