f%2020%20and%20to%20rival%20Western%20powers%20in%20clubs%20like%20the%20BRICS.%20Some%20are%20driven%20by%20pragmatic%20self-interest%2C%20focusing%20on%20energy%2C%20trade%20or%20economic%20considerations.%20For%20others%2C%20military%20cooperation%20or%20weapons%20lie%20at%20the%20heart%20of%20the%20entente.%20More%20often%20than%20not%2C%20they%20share%20a%20common%20outlook%20with%20Russia%20%E2%80%94%20a%20desire%20to%20supplant%20the%20post-Cold%20War%2C%20US-led%20world%20order.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EChina%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20Russia%20Gets%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20China%20has%20been%20a%20diplomatic%20and%20economic%20lifeline%20for%20Moscow.%20Russia%20has%20been%20buying%20electronics%2C%20industrial%20equipment%20and%20cars%2C%20while%20selling%20its%20Asian%20neighbor%20oil%20and%20gas%2C%20even%20if%20%E2%80%94%20as%20with%20gas%20%E2%80%94%20it's%20at%20a%20discount%20to%20what%20it%20once%20earned%20from%20supplying%20Europe.%20Bilateral%20trade%20reached%20a%20record%20%24240%20billion%20in%202023.%20But%20it's%20having%20a%20powerful%20partner%20that%20shares%20the%20Kremlin's%20goal%20of%20challenging%20the%20US-led%20order%20and%20shutting%20Washington-led%20alliances%20out%20of%20what%20they%20consider%20their%20sphere%20of%20influence%20that%20Moscow%20may%20prize%20most.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20China%20Gets%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EBeijing%2C%20too%2C%20relishes%20having%20another%20powerful%20authoritarian%20state%20by%20its%20side%20as%20it%20seeks%20to%20re-shape%20the%20international%20order.%20Russia%20and%20China%20have%20increasingly%20coordinated%20their%20positions%20at%20the%20United%20Nations%20Security%20Council%2C%20where%20both%20wield%20vetoes%2C%20and%20made%20common%20cause%20against%20the%20US.%20Military%20cooperation%20is%20deepening%20and%20Russia%20has%20sold%20China%20some%20of%20its%20most%20advanced%20weapons%20systems.%20A%20Russian%20victory%20in%20Ukraine%20would%20weaken%20US%20influence%20as%20China%20mulls%20its%20ambitions%20over%20Taiwan%2C%20which%20it%20claims%20as%20its%20own.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESaudi%20Arabia%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20Russia%20Gets%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20First%20and%20foremost%2C%20Russia%20helps%20shape%20the%20global%20oil%20market%20and%20maximize%20crucial%20revenue%20for%20the%20Kremlin%20through%20the%20OPEC%2B%20alliance%20of%20crude-producing%20nations%2C%20which%20the%20two%20countries%20dominate.%20Saudi%20Arabia%20went%20out%20of%20its%20way%20in%20not%20condemning%20Russia%20after%20the%20start%20of%20the%20war.%20Putin%20also%20paid%20the%20Kingdom%20a%20visit%20in%20December%20in%20a%20rare%20foray%20abroad%20that%20demonstrated%20he%20was%20still%20welcome%20in%20some%20parts%20of%20the%20globe.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20Saudi%20Arabia%20Gets%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EAside%20from%20the%20OPEC%2B%20partnership%2C%20Saudi%20Arabia%20has%20benefited%20from%20Russian%20help%20in%20avoiding%20pariah%20status.%20Putin%20was%20one%20of%20the%20few%20leaders%20to%20embrace%20Crown%20Prince%20Mohammed%20bin%20Salman%20with%20smiles%20and%20high-fives%20at%20a%202018%20G-20%20summit%20two%20months%20after%20agents%20from%20his%20country%20murdered%20Washington%20Post%20columnist%20Jamal%20Khashoggi.%20US%20President%20Joe%20Biden%20has%20since%20reversed%20course%20on%20an%20earlier%20vow%20to%20isolate%20Riyadh%20over%20Khashoggi's%20killing%20and%20sought%20to%20shore%20up%20the%20two%20countries'%20alliance.%20But%20as%20Saudi%20foreign%20policy%20is%20increasingly%20transactional%20and%20driven%20by%20economic%20interests%2C%20ties%20with%20Moscow%20are%20only%20likely%20to%20deepen.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ETurkey%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20Russia%20Gets%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EPutin%20juggles%20geopolitical%20rivalry%20with%20Turkish%20President%20Recep%20Tayyip%20Erdogan%20in%20places%20like%20Syria%2C%20Libya%20and%20the%20Caucasus%20region%2C%20while%20fostering%20trade%20to%20its%20third-largest%20export%20market%20last%20year.%20Turkey%20has%20also%20become%20a%20key%20hub%20for%20indirect%20imports%20of%20sanctioned%20goods%20that%20Russia%20seeks%2C%20and%20a%20help%20for%20Putin%20to%20keep%20his%20country's%20global%20ties.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20Turkey%20Gets%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EWhile%20siding%20with%20Ukraine%20in%20the%20war%2C%20Erdogan%20has%20refused%20to%20join%20sanctions%20on%20Russia%20which%20is%20a%20major%20gas%20supplier%20to%20Turkey%20and%20is%20constructing%20its%20first%20nuclear%20power%20plant.%20Turkey's%20tourism%20and%20agriculture%20industries%20rely%20heavily%20on%20the%20Russian%20market.%20Erdogan%20has%20positioned%20himself%20as%20a%20self-declared%20mediator%20between%20Ukraine%20and%20Russia%2C%20helping%20to%20broker%20deals%20on%20grain%20shipments%20and%20prisoner%20swaps.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIran%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20Russia%20Gets%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3ERussia%20turned%20to%20Iran%20for%20drones%20to%20aid%20its%20war%20in%20Ukraine%20and%20is%20building%20a%20trade%20route%20with%20Tehran%20connecting%20to%20India%20that%20may%20help%20weaken%20the%20impact%20of%20international%20sanctions.%20Russian%20and%20Iranian%20officials%20have%20discussed%20boosting%20financial%20and%20banking%20cooperation%20to%20ease%20sanctions%20pressure%2C%20as%20Moscow%20learns%20from%20Tehran's%20experience%20of%20decades%20in%20isolation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20Iran%20Gets%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Iran%20is%20looking%20to%20Russia%20for%20weapons%20including%20air-defense%20systems%20and%20fighter%20jets%20to%20replace%20outdated%20equipment.%20It%20also%20relied%20on%20Moscow%20to%20build%20its%20Bushehr%20nuclear%20power%20plant.%20Tehran%20joined%20with%20Russia%20to%20support%20President%20Bashar%20al-Assad%20in%20Syria's%20war%20and%20shares%20Moscow's%20hostility%20to%20the%20US%20presence%20in%20the%20Middle%20East.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIndia%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20Russia%20Gets%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EIndia%2C%20the%20world's%20third-largest%20crude%20consumer%2C%20has%20been%20a%20major%20buyer%20of%20discounted%20Russian%20oil%20since%20the%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine%2C%20but%20tighter%20enforcement%20of%20US%20sanctions%20that%20seek%20to%20choke%20off%20the%20flow%20of%20petrodollars%20to%20Kremlin%20coffers%20is%20now%20disrupting%20supplies.%20The%20relationship%20with%20India%20confers%20legitimacy%20on%20Russia%20as%20it%20courts%20the%20so-called%20Global%20South.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20India%20Gets%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EDiscounted%20oil%2C%20but%20Russia%20has%20also%20been%20a%20long-time%20and%20trusted%20supplier%20of%20weapons.%20Moscow%20has%20been%20willing%20to%20help%20the%20South%20Asian%20nation%20by%20using%20its%20veto%20power%20at%20the%20UN%20Security%20Council%20to%20back%20Indian%20interests.%20Strong%20ties%20with%20Russia%20also%20provide%20a%20counterbalance%20to%20other%20major%20global%20powers%2C%20helping%20India%20maintain%20strategic%20autonomy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBrazil%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20Russia%20Gets%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3ERussia%20benefits%20diplomatically%20from%20ties%20with%20Latin%20America's%20largest%20economy%20and%20the%20relative%20leadership%20it%20has%20in%20the%20region.%20Brazil%20is%20a%20founding%20member%20with%20Russia%20of%20the%20BRICS%20group%20of%20countries.%20Brazilian%20President%20Luiz%20Inacio%20Lula%20da%20Silva%20has%20so%20far%20sought%20to%20position%20his%20country%20as%20a%20neutral%20nation%20that%20can%20maintain%20ties%20with%20both%20Russia%20and%20Ukraine%20and%20has%20repeatedly%20rejected%20calls%20to%20send%20arms%20to%20Kyiv%2C%20arguing%20that%20the%20US%20and%20European%20Union%20strategy%20is%20undermining%20the%20prospect%20of%20a%20negotiated%20solution.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20Brazil%20Gets%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EOn%20the%20trade%20front%2C%20Brazil%20gets%20imports%20of%20Russian%20fertilizer%2C%20as%20well%20as%20diesel%20and%20oil%20products.%20More%20importantly%2C%20Brazil%20gets%20a%20partner%20in%20efforts%20to%20reshape%20the%20US-led%20global%20order%3B%20Lula%20has%20long%20pushed%20for%20reforms%20to%20global%20institutions%20like%20the%20IMF%20in%20order%20to%20make%20them%20more%20representative%20of%20the%20Global%20South.%20But%20even%20aside%20from%20Lula%2C%20Brazilian%20leaders%20have%20long%20found%20in%20Russia%20a%20safe%20and%20uncritical%20ally.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHungary%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20Russia%20Gets%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EPrime%20Minister%20Viktor%20Orban's%20government%20has%20maintained%20close%20ties%20with%20Putin%2C%20with%20the%20Hungarian%20leader%20meeting%20his%20Russian%20counterpart%20in%20Beijing%20last%20October.%20That%20has%20provided%20Putin%20an%20ally%20within%20the%20EU%20who%20has%20variously%20held%20up%20financial%20aid%20for%20Ukraine%2C%20threatened%20to%20scuttle%20Kyiv's%20membership%20talks%20with%20the%20bloc%20and%20even%20delayed%20by%20more%20than%20a%20year%20NATO%20accession%20for%20Sweden.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20Hungary%20Gets%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EEnergy.%20Hungary%20is%20one%20of%20the%20few%20EU%20nations%20still%20receiving%20Russian%20gas%2C%20and%20Russia's%20Rosatom%20nuclear%20corporation%20retains%20a%20lead%20role%20in%20expanding%20its%20sole%20atomic%20power%20plant.%20Meanwhile%2C%20Orban%2C%20who's%20declared%20a%20brand%20of%20%26quot%3Billiberal%20democracy%2C%26quot%3B%20gets%20backing%20for%20his%20ideological%20alternative%20to%20the%20US-led%20international%20order.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESouth%20Africa%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20Russia%20Gets%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3ESouth%20African%20President%20Cyril%20Ramaphosa%20has%20refused%20to%20condemn%20Putin%20over%20the%20war%2C%20or%20back%20United%20Nations%20resolutions%20censuring%20Moscow%20for%20the%20invasion.%20The%20two%20nations%20are%20both%20members%20of%20BRICS%20and%20its%20forums%20have%20provided%20an%20opportunity%20for%20their%20leaders%20to%20regularly%20interact.%20Ramaphosa%20did%20persuade%20Putin%20to%20skip%20a%20BRICS%20summit%20in%20Johannesburg%20last%20year%20and%20participate%20virtually%20instead%2C%20sparing%20Pretoria%20from%20having%20to%20decide%20whether%20to%20arrest%20him%20under%20the%20ICC%20warrant.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20South%20Africa%20Gets%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EWhile%20trade%20between%20Russia%20and%20South%20Africa%20is%20negligible%2C%20they%20have%20long-standing%20historical%20ties%20that%20stem%20from%20the%20proactive%20stance%20the%20Soviet%20Union%20took%20against%20White-minority%20rule.%20A%20number%20of%20senior%20members%20of%20the%20African%20National%20Congress%20sought%20sanctuary%20and%20underwent%20military%20training%20in%20Russia%20during%20the%20apartheid%20era.%20Russian%20companies%20were%20in%20the%20running%20to%20build%20new%20nuclear%20power%20plants%20in%20South%20Africa%20during%20former%20President%20Jacob%20Zuma's%20tenure%2C%20although%20plans%20to%20issue%20a%20contract%20have%20been%20on%20ice%20since%20Ramaphosa%20took%20office%20in%202018%20due%20to%20cost.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERussia%20has%20also%20sought%20to%20build%20good%20will%20in%20Africa%20through%20security%20assistance%2C%20arms%20and%20grain%20%E2%80%94%20food%20supplies%20that%2C%20in%20part%2C%20were%20cut%20off%20because%20its%20war%20in%20Ukraine%20threatened%20Black%20Sea%20shipping.%20In%20turn%2C%20Russia%20wants%20access%20to%20markets%20and%20new%20allies%20that%20can%20soften%20the%20impact%20of%20sanctions%2C%20and%20expand%20its%20military%20influence%20at%20the%20expense%20of%20Western%20powers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20burgeoning%20friendship%20with%20Kim%20Jong%20Un%20has%20also%20benefited%20Russia.%20The%20US%2C%20South%20Korea%20and%20others%20allege%20that%20North%20Korea%20is%20sending%20massive%20amounts%20of%20artillery%20shells%20as%20well%20as%20short-range%20nuclear-capable%20ballistic%20missiles.%20In%20return%2C%20Russia%20is%20accused%20of%20providing%20Pyongyang%20with%20food%2C%20raw%20materials%20and%20parts%20used%20in%20weapons%20manufacturing.%20Russia%20also%20vetoed%20a%20UN%20Security%20Council%20resolution%20to%20extend%20a%20panel%20of%20experts%20that%20reports%20on%20North%20Korea's%20nuclear%20arsenal%20developments.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOther%20countries%20like%20the%20United%20Arab%20Emirates%2C%20where%20tens%20of%20thousands%20of%20Russians%20made%20a%20home%20after%20the%20outbreak%20of%20war%2C%20and%20Egypt%20as%20well%20as%20old%20allies%20such%20as%20Venezuela%20and%20Cuba%20have%20also%20maintained%20ties.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20now%2C%20despite%20the%20best%20efforts%20by%20the%20US%20and%20its%20allies%2C%20Russia%20remains%20anything%20but%20isolated.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1716024420000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-05%2F9t6jh3to_putin-bloomberg_625x300_18_May_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fhow-putin-friends-are-helping-russia-upend-the-us-led-world-order-5691040%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Vladimir%20Putin%20is%20wrapping%20up%20a%20trip%20to%20China%2C%20where%20his%20warm%20ties%20with%20President%20Xi%20Jinping%20have%20led%20to%20booming%20trade%20and%20increasing%20defense%20coordination.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fhow-putin-friends-are-helping-russia-upend-the-us-led-world-order-5691040%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fhow-putin-friends-are-helping-russia-upend-the-us-led-world-order-5691040%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news